== Description ==

The '''BIM Rewire''' tool takes selected objects (lines, edges, or wire segments) and attempts to reconnect them into continuous [[Draft_Wire|wires]]. This is useful when you have fragmented line work that should form connected polylines, for example after importing geometry from other applications or after splitting operations.

== Usage ==

# Select two or more objects that contain only straight edges (lines, wires, or shapes with edges).
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → [[Image:BIM_Rewire.svg|16px]] Rewire}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|R}} then {{KEY|W}}.
# One or more [[Draft_Wire|Draft Wire]] objects are created from the connected edge sequences. The original objects are deleted.

== Notes ==

* The tool does not create closed wires.


